-- Colombia Stock Movers: Cementos Argos, Canacol Energy, Exito
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-02-06T21:09:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/colombia-stock-movers-cementos-argos-canacol-energy-exito.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.1 percent to 13,940.14, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.1 percent to 1,642.15.  Cementos Argos SA (CEMARGOS)  , the country’s biggest
cement maker, rose 1.1 percent to 10,980 pesos. The Medellin-
based company plans to invest $120 million this year in Colombia
and abroad, its press office said in an e-mail today.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in Colombia, dropped 3.4 percent to
1,545 pesos. The company said in a statement late Feb. 3 that it
will abandon the Chachalote-1 well in Colombia after tests were
completed.  Morgan Stanley said in a report today it raised its growth
forecast for Colombia this year to 6.7 percent from a previous
forecast of 4.1 percent.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  , the nation’s biggest
publicly-traded retailer, rose 0.5 percent to 25,140 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
